          {
            "text": "A five-minute daytime tapping practice from Day 30 of a 30-day sleep programme. Day 30 theme: claim rest as a birthright. The daytime tap closes the programme by marking what changed: the nervous system that learned safety, the nights that became familiar, the relationship with the body that shifted from opposition to trust. The reframe names it as arrival, not the end of a programme but the beginning of a new normal.",
            "type": "text"
          }
